  <summary>10/5/2001--Introduced.
Visa Information Security Act of 2001 - Amends the Immigration and Nationality Act to require: (1) a nonimmigrant visa applicant to provide machine readable biometric identifiers (fingerprints or handprints), which shall be database-checked for criminal information prior to visa approval; (2) port of entry matching of such identifiers with the applicant prior to U.S. admission; and (3) establishment of a related fee.</summary>
